---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Picture } from "astro:assets";
import neil_rogers_show from "../assets/neil-rogers-show.jpg";
---

<Layout
	title="Neil Rogers - Listen to the Neil Rogers Show Podcast"
	description="Listen to the Neil Rogers Show Podcast"
	url="/listen/"
>
	<div class="card">
		<h1>üëÇüèΩ Podcast</h1>

		<p>
			<b>The Neil Rogers Show</b> is available as a daily podcast. A show is released each morning. All
			the shows can also be downloaded directly from the resources on our <a href="/audio/">Audio</a
			> page.
		</p>
	</div>

	<h3>Listen to the Neil Rogers Podcast on:</h3>
	<div>
		<ul>
			<li>
				<a
					href="https://music.amazon.com/podcasts/299b0ce8-1edf-4a9e-bb16-6c1fa63bfc90/Neil-Rogers-Show?"
				>
					Amazon Music
				</a>
			</li>
			<li><a href="https://castbox.fm/channel/Neil-Rogers-Show-id539213">Castbox</a></li>
			<li>
				<a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/neil-rogers-show/id1231601174">iTunes</a>
			</li>
			<li><a href="https://open.spotify.com/show/2eQORHonddaXiNLPrVDbH3">Spotify</a></li>
			<li><a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/NeilRogersShow">Podcast RSS</a></li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			If your podcast provider does not have the <b>Neil Rogers Show</b>, email <b
				>audio@neilrogers.org</b
			> or message <b>@NeilRogersRadio</b> on X, and we'll work to add it.
		</p>
	</div>

	<h3>Neil Rogers Podcast Schedule</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>MONDAY 1986-1989</li>
		<li>TUESDAY 1990-1997</li>
		<li>WEDNESDAY 1998-2001</li>
		<li>THURSDAY 2002-2003</li>
		<li>FRIDAY 2004-2005</li>
		<li>SATURDAY 2006-2007</li>
		<li>SUNDAY 2008-2009</li>
	</ul>

	<div class="image-container">
		<Picture
			src={neil_rogers_show}
			formats={["avif", "webp"]}
			alt="Neil Rogers Show"
			class="neo-image"
		/>
		<div class="image-caption">Neil Rogers Show</div>
	</div>

	<h3>Podcast Availability</h3>

	<h3>100% Non-Commercial</h3>
	<p>
		These podcasts and our YouTube channel are a hobby and not a business. We do not accept
		sponsors. Do not reach out to us with a proposal to monetize either. Neil died in 2010, so don't
		ask to be interviewed on the podcast. Your email will be blocked, marked as SPAM, and deleted.
	</p>

	<h3>South Florida Radio Archives</h3>
	<p>Our 2nd podcast "South Florida Radio Archives" is no longer active.</p>
</Layout>
